{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"3c66fcc5-f2a2-4a2f-af81-421d01725931","content":"Here are the MSBuild evaluation performance issues in this project:\n\n---\n\n**1. Deep Import Chain** (`EvalHeavy.csproj` → `level1.props` → `level2.props` → `level3.props`)\n\nEach `<Import>` adds file I/O and XML parsing during evaluation. Deeply nested imports compound evaluation time. Flatten where possible.\n\n**2. Expensive Property Function — File I/O at Evaluation Time** (line 13)\n\n```xml\n<BuildNotes>$([System.IO.File]::ReadAllText('build-notes.txt'))</BuildNotes>\n```\n\nThis reads a file into a property *during evaluation*. File I/O in property functions blocks the evaluator and runs on every design-time build (IDE load, IntelliSense refresh, etc.). Move file reads to a target that runs only at build time.\n\n**3. Overly Broad Glob** (line 9)\n\n```xml\n<AdditionalFiles Include=\"**\\*.*\" Exclude=\"**\\bin\\**;**\\obj\\**\" />\n```\n\nA recursive wildcard glob (`**\\*.*`) forces MSBuild to enumerate the entire directory tree during evaluation. As the repo grows, this becomes increasingly expensive. Scope the glob to specific extensions or directories.\n\n---\n\n**Summary of fixes:**\n| Issue | Recommendation |\n|-------|---------------|\n| Nested imports (3 levels) | Flatten into one `.props` file |\n| `File::ReadAllText` in property | Move to a build-time target |\n| `**\\*.*` glob | Narrow to specific file types/paths |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a37ebbc0-a87c-44f1-ad85-9fc7d6c16ba0","outputTokens":378,"requestId":"1C35:102F9F:A91553:C67137:69F400E3"},"id":"7dd162ef-09f6-4181-bdef-e6c9c7514e3f","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:25:02.975Z","parentId":"43655d1d-e487-405e-ae96-c86e73d0421e"}
